 <section><title>Illustrations</title>
     <section><title>Formal Figures</title>
         <para>Formal Figures have titles and figure numbers</para>
         <figure id="Fig01" xreflabel = "Figure 1.1"><title>A Multistability Illusion</title>
             <mediaobject>
                 <imageobject>
                     <imagedata fileref="figures/1280px-Multistability.svg.png" scale="30"/>
                 </imageobject>
                 <textobject><phrase>An example of a figure.</phrase></textobject>
             </mediaobject> 
         </figure>
         <para>To insert a figure reference, you must 1) add an id attribute in the figure tag and 2) insert an xref xml tag where you want the reference. For example, look at the code to see how I inserted the following referecne to my cross-reference text: <xref linkend="Fig01"/></para>
     </section>
